	</div><h1 class=3D"entry-title">Air Flow Conversion Calculator</h1>		</hea=
der>
=09
	<div class=3D"entry-content is-layout-constrained">
		<p class=3D"single-excerpt">Calculate the air flow past a point in a rect=
angular or circular duct per unit of time.</p>	=09

   =20


   =20


    <div>
        <p>Air Velocity is measurement of the rate of displacement of air o=
r gas at a specific location.</p>
        <p>Air velocity (distance traveled per unit of time) is usually exp=
ressed in Linear Feet per Minute
        (LFM). By multiplying air velocity by the cross section area of a
        duct, you can determine the air volume flowing past a point in
        the duct per unit of time. Volume flow is usually measured in
        Cubic Feet per Minute (CFM).</p>
        <p>Concept of Air Velocity can be used in air conditioning, heating=
and ventilating work. </p>
        <p><strong>Enter value, select unit and click on calculate. Result =
will be displayed.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div>
        <form name=3D"cv_air" id=3D"cv_air">
           =20
            <div class=3D"row">
                <h4>Enter Your Values:</h4>
            </div>

            <div class=3D"row air-flow-container">
                <div>
                    <label for=3D"in_air">Air Flow</label>
                    <input type=3D"text" size=3D"7" maxlength=3D"10" name=
=3D"in_air" id=3D"in_air">
                </div>
   =20
                <div>
                    <select name=3D"in_unit1" size=3D"1">
                        <option>LFM</option>
                        <option>m/s</option>
                        <option>MPH</option>
                        <option>CFM</option>
                        <option>m^3/hr</option>
                        <option>L/s</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class=3D"row">
                <div class=3D"duct-containter">
                    <div>
                        <input type=3D"checkbox" id=3D"rect_duct" name=3D"d=
uct_type" value=3D"rect">
                        <label for=3D"rect_duct">Rectangle Duct</label>
                    </div>
       =20
                    <div>
                        <label for=3D"h_duct">H:</label>
                        <input type=3D"text" size=3D"5" name=3D"h_duct" id=
=3D"h_duct">
                    </div>
       =20
                    <div>
                        <label for=3D"w_duct">W:</label>
                        <input type=3D"text" size=3D"5" name=3D"w_duct" id=
=3D"w_duct">
                    </div>
       =20
                    <div>
                        <select name=3D"in_unit3" size=3D"1">
                            <option>in</option>
                            <option>ft</option>
                            <option>mm</option>
                            <option>cm</option>
                            <option>m</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class=3D"duct-containter">
                    <div>
                        <input type=3D"checkbox" id=3D"circ_duct" name=3D"d=
uct_type" value=3D"circle">
                        <label for=3D"circ_duct">Circular Duct</label>
                    </div>
       =20
                    <div>
                        <label for=3D"r_duct">R:</label>
                        <input type=3D"text" size=3D"5" name=3D"r_duct" id=
=3D"r_duct">
                    </div>
       =20
                    <div>
                        <select name=3D"in_unit2" size=3D"1">
                            <option>in</option>
                            <option>ft</option>
                            <option>mm</option>
                            <option>cm</option>
                            <option>m</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>
                </div>     =20
            </div>
          =20

